remperl -- Remote Perl
----------------------

Run Perl scripts on remote machines over any pipe-based transport, with transparent
dependency injection and both CLI and library interfaces.

remperl connects to a remote Perl interpreter through an arbitrary pipe command,
bootstraps a protocol client on the remote end, and then executes Perl code there.
If module serving is enabled, missing modules are fetched transparently from the
local machine on demand; the remote machine needs no pre-installed dependencies
beyond a bare Perl interpreter.

See "perldoc remperl" for CLI reference and "perldoc Remote::Perl" for the library API.

Requirements
------------

  Local:  Perl 5.36+
  Remote: bare Perl 5.10+ (no modules needed beyond core)
